                              <p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">Hi rodri=
go-f-p@hotmail.com</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">We are writing to inform you about an =
</span><strong>update to our Inactive Accounts and Database Maintenance Pol=
icy at Kinguin</strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">. This email expla=
ins </span><strong>how the policy works and how it may apply to your accoun=
t</strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">. You can find the full T&amp;C=
 attached to this email.</span></p>
<p><strong>What are the main changes?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400;" aria-level=3D"1"><strong>Account Freeze</st=
rong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">: Accounts without transactions for =
</span><strong>24 months</strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> may be =
frozen to prevent potential security risks. Frozen accounts cannot be acces=
sed or participate in campaigns but can be reactivated by contacting Custom=
er Support.</span></li>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400;" aria-level=3D"1"><strong>Account Deactivati=
on</strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">: Accounts inactive for </span=
><strong>36 months</strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> may be deacti=
vated. Deactivation disables access to Account features and archives Accoun=
t and transaction records in a restricted archive for legal, security and a=
ccounting purposes.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400;" aria-level=3D"1"><strong>Notifications</str=
ong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">: Before any freeze or deactivation, =
you will </span><strong>always </strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">r=
eceive </span><strong>advance email notifications</strong><span style=3D"fo=
nt-weight: 400;">, giving you ample time to take action.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li style=3D"font-weight: 400;" aria-level=3D"1"><strong>Database Maintenan=
ce</strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">: To optimize platform perform=
ance, we may delete data during yearly maintenance. Affected users will rec=
eive notifications at least 3 months&nbsp; in advance with instructions on =
how to back up their data.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Keeping your account active:</strong></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">To maintain Account active status, ple=
ase complete a transaction on Kinguin.net. All fully processed operations a=
re valid, excluding those cancelled e.g. due to non-payment, chargebacks, o=
r withdrawals.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">=F0=9F=91=89 Remember: freezing and de=
activation of inactive accounts take place once per year, on </span><strong=
>December 31st</strong><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">If you have any questions contact our =
Customer Support at <a href=3D"https://support.kinguin.net/hc/en-us">https:=
//support.kinguin.net/hc/en-us</a>.</span></p>
<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"><em>This email is a mandatory legal/se=
rvice communication about your Kinguin account and Balance, sent under our =
Inactive Accounts and Database Maintenance Policy. It is not marketing. As =
long as your Kinguin account remains open, you will continue to receive suc=
h mandatory notices. If you no longer wish to receive mandatory account ema=
ils, you can request closure of your Kinguin account by contacting our Supp=
ort team or gdpr@kinguin.<span style=3D"color: #000000;">net.</span></em></=
span></p>

                                 <p>Best regards,<br>Kinguin Support Team</=
p>
